cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with parallelization of tasks on multiprocessors.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the adaptation of a canonical schedule for DVFS multiprocessor platforms.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with meeting real-time constraints and minimizing energy in a system.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm via simulations.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is also relevant as the paper deals with energy minimization in a real-time system.
